Raw dev notes -- Invoice Processing System: Gemini + Google Sheets for Priority ERP (March 2026)

Built a complete invoice processing system for a client. PDFs come in via email or Google Drive,
get processed by Gemini (Flash with Pro fallback), and output tab-delimited files for Priority ERP.
The whole thing runs on Google Apps Script.

Architecture:
- DriveWatcher scans inbox folder for new PDFs
- Gemini 2.5 Flash extracts structured data (supplier, amounts, line items)
- Smart fallback to Gemini Pro when Flash fails (bad HP numbers, missing fields, totals mismatch)
- Results stored in Google Sheets with status tracking
- TXT files generated in Priority ERP format
- Customer web dashboard (GAS Web App) with Hebrew UI

Key challenges:
- Multi-invoice PDFs: had to split, extract unique invoice numbers, merge duplicates
- Hebrew supplier names and RTL rendering
- HP (company ID) validation: exactly 9 digits, pad if shorter
- Gemini hallucinating invoice dates -- added dynamic year range validation
- Google Apps Script 6-minute timeout: built checkpoint/resume system
- Tab-delimited format with DD/MM/YY dates for Priority compatibility

Smart features:
- Thinking mode (thinkBudget: -1) for better extraction accuracy
- Save both Flash and Pro responses for comparison
- Audit script: recursive scan, MD5 dedup, missing file diagnosis
- Per-status guidance in the dashboard UI
- Fallback chain for expense_account and SKU codes

This went from "just parse some PDFs" to a full accounts-payable automation. Scope creep
is real but the client is happy.

Next: Status review workflow, automated supplier matching improvements.
